<title>GREECE: NATL BANK SELLS HALYPS METALLURGY TO SOVEL.</title>
<headline>NATL BANK SELLS HALYPS METALLURGY TO SOVEL.</headline>
<dateline>ATHENS 1996-09-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Halyps Metallurgy which has been dormant for five years has been sold by National Bank subsidiary National Capital to Sovel, the bank said on Friday.</p>
<p>&quot;Sovel's major shareholders include Viohalko and National Bank with a 15 percent stake. It starts with a share capital of 8.0 billion drachmas and the investment will reach 18 billion,&quot; National Bank said in a statement.</p>
<p>Halyps Metallurgy's plant in Almyros will resume operations soon offering employment opportunities in Magnisia, the bank said. --George Georgiopoulos, Athens Newsroom +301 3311812-4</p>
